  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it was not really a hospital.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was in one of the buildings of the original German Army camp that has been outside of the little town of Bergen for many, many years.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The British Army, who was the main army that liberated that part of Germany with the Canadians-- although it was mostly British Army-- I don't know which army it was.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Second Army, it could have been.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They took over the German Army base camp and the room-- a large room-- that had been turned into the hospital facility.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "What I mean by that, there were all iron bedsteads, and I was in one of those beds, as was my sister and the other children of our [? diamond ?] group.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I don't remember how long I was in the hospital bed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Maurice, I found it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I don't remember how long I was in the hospital bed.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I remember a lady came to my-- a nurse came to my bedside.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I spoke a few words of English, not many, although she was a Dutch lady.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I always remembered and to this day, her name.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Her name, her last name-- I don't remember her first name-- was Jahemstahl.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Jahemstahl the family Jahemstahl-- it's a German name-- and before the war, I knew that the family Jahemstahl had been in Holland in a publishing business.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she must have been related to that family.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Because my mother had taught my sister and I to memorize my grandmother's address in England, in London, I asked her-- this Dutch lady, Jewish Dutch lady of German descent with that name who was connected to the Red Cross with the British Army-- I asked her if she could find my grandmother, get in touch with my grandmother in England.",
      "word_count": 61
    }
  ],
